org.epics.pvData.pvCopy
Interface PVCopy

public interface PVCopy

This interface maps between a PVRecord and a PVStructure that holds a copy of a subset of the data in the PVRecord.

Author:
mrk

getStructure

Structure getStructure()
Get the introspection interface for the set of fields describing the subset of the fields from PVRecord which a PVStructure contains.

Returns:
The introspection interface.

createPVStructure

PVStructure createPVStructure()
Create a PVStructure which can hold a subset od the data from the PVRecord. A client may require multiple PVStructures. For example if a monitor request supports a queue than a PVStructure is required for each queue element.

Returns:
The interface.

getCopyOffset

int getCopyOffset(PVField recordPVField)
Given a PVField from the record determine the offset within the PVStructure where copy of the data is located. PVStructure.getSubField(offset) can be called to locate the PVField within the PVStructure.

Parameters:
recordPVField - The PVField within PVREcord.
Returns:
The offset or -1 if the field in the record does not have a copy in the PVStructure.

getCopyOffset

int getCopyOffset(PVStructure recordPVStructure,
                  PVField recordPVField)
Given a recordPVField within a recordPVStructure determine the offset within the PVStructure where copy of the data is located. PVStructure.getSubField(offset) can be called to locate the PVField within the PVStructure.

Parameters:
recordPVStructure - The PVStructure within the PVRecord.
recordPVField - The PVField within the recordPVStructure.
Returns:
The offset or -1 if the field in the record does not have a copy in the PVStructure.

initCopy

void initCopy(PVStructure copyPVStructure,
              java.util.BitSet bitSet)
Initialize PVStructure with then current data from the PVRecord. The bitSet will have offset 0 set to 1 and all other bits set to 0.

Parameters:
copyPVStructure - The PVStructure.
bitSet - The bitSet for PVStructure.

updateCopy

boolean updateCopy(PVStructure copyPVStructure,
                   java.util.BitSet bitSet)
Update PVStructure from PVRecord. The BitSet will show which fields in PVStructure have changed.

Parameters:
copyPVStructure - The PVStructure.
bitSet - The BitSet which shows the fields that were modified.
Returns:
(false,true) if (no fields, at least one) field was modified.

updateRecord

boolean updateRecord(PVStructure copyPVStructure,
                     java.util.BitSet bitSet)
Update the fields in PVRecord with data from PVStructure. Only fields that have the offset in bitSet set to true are modified.

Parameters:
copyPVStructure - The PVStructure.
bitSet - The offsets within PVStructure that have new data.
Returns:
false,true) if (no fields, at least one) field was modified.

checkBitSet

boolean checkBitSet(java.util.BitSet bitSet)
Check the bits in BitSet. If any PVStructure has all it;s fields modified then the offset for the structure itself is set to true and the offset for ALL the fields within the structure are set false.

Parameters:
bitSet - The bitSet
Returns:
(false,true) if any offsets are true.
